cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about named entity recognition (NER) from electronic medical records, which is a natural language processing (NLP) task. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also proposes a transfer learning framework, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves feature representation and parameter transfer, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE), respectively.
